fields.Title: INVENTORY / STOCK CERTIFICATE
fields.Description: Read the Stock Certificate traded with MRLBG

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "The scrawl across the paper opens w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The scrawl across the paper opens wide its many grins back at you. A mess of mouths ready to swallow you up. Intertwined and interflowing, impenetrably. Your eyes begin to water.

fields.Title: Logic: "Focus on the negative space -- this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Focus on the negative space -- this will tell you the parameters of each letter. Isolate each one and *decipher*.

fields.Title: Hand/Eye Coordination: "Feisty little thing! But don't worr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Feisty little thing! But don't worry -- it's under control.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Devious use of Swish there. It's a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Devious use of Swish there. It's a font literally *designed* to win legal agreements by way of being almost unreadable through flamboyance.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "You can do this. Maybe squinting wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can do this. Maybe squinting will help?

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "Each letter is shaped like a laugh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Each letter is shaped like a laugh line being pulled in a million different  directions. They're all grinning at you -- pleased with practically being indecipherable.

fields.Title: You: "Focus on the header."
fields.Dialogue Text: Focus on the header.

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "A bold, black mesh curves around th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A bold, black mesh curves around the oval image at the top of the document. It almost looks as if it were penned with intention. Perhaps it was. You're starting to think it might actually *say* something.

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "Slowly, it happens -- individual le..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Slowly, it happens -- individual letters coalesce. It's like watching ice melt to reveal the shrubs underneath. A few seconds later and you can read the entire heading: M -- K -- M -- G. This is a start. Can you read the rest?

fields.Title: You: "Phew! Reading is hard. That's enoug..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Phew! Reading is hard. That's enough for now.

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "Oh brother, you have tumbled into a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh brother, you have tumbled into a *chophouse* of words. This is where letters come to die. A pile of discarded alphabet limbs lie before you in spidery formation. Why are they all so hairy?

fields.Title: You: "[Put it away.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Put it away.]

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "The certificate threatens to coil b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The certificate threatens to coil back into itself as you relax a little.

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "You start to carefully shave it all..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You start to carefully shave it all with your razor eyes. A few 'R's stick out. There's an 'E'. Then, suddenly, some whole words appear: 'This certifies that (unreadable) is entitled (unreadable) in the capital stock of Mauer-Koshlai Mercury Group.'

fields.Title: You: "Look at the top of the document."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the top of the document.

fields.Title: You: "Attempt to read the words."
fields.Dialogue Text: Attempt to read the words.

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "Your vision blurs into a haze of da..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your vision blurs into a haze of dark scribbles. It's like looking at a wrought iron fence through a greasy lens. Not a single recognisable symbol appears to you.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "That really didn't help, did it? Ho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That really didn't help, did it? How about opening your eyes as wide as possible?

fields.Title: Logic: "Start with the biggest letters in o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Start with the biggest letters in order to learn the characteristics of the style. Then work your way down.

fields.Title: You: "Open them wide."
fields.Dialogue Text: Open them wide.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "I know business-speak when I see it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I know business-speak when I see it. This is an official, legitimate, checked-by-the-board certificate. You really are a stock market big-boy now. Sound the money klaxon and bring out the hustle-clowns -- they dance for us today!

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "An underground kingdom of shimmerin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An underground kingdom of shimmering spillways! Silver stars melted down and filtered for their precious discharge. What a place of inspiration!

fields.Title: Logic: "There must be *some* form of logic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There must be *some* form of logic hidden away in there...

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "The pearlescent paper adamantly res..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The pearlescent paper adamantly resists being held open -- it demands struggle at both ends. The print inside is just as taxing due to its fine and curlicued font. The most attractive part is the image emblazoned across the top.

fields.Title: You: "Squint in hope of seeing something..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Squint in hope of seeing something within the lines.

fields.Title: You: "Give it up. (Go back.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: Give it up. (Go back.)

fields.Title: You: "Nah. (Give up.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: Nah. (Give up.)

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Okay, okay -- enough of that. It's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay, okay -- enough of that. It's starting to sting. Better try another approach.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Her form is terrible! She needs to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Her form is terrible! She needs to straighten her back and increase the downward pressure on that machine. Has *no one* taught her about ergonomics?

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "If it does, it remains hidden from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If it does, it remains hidden from you. All you see is a baffling enigma, a coiled nest of viper-letters -- if they even *are* letters.

fields.Title: You: "Try to read the tiny print."
fields.Dialogue Text: Try to read the tiny print.

fields.Title: Stock Certificate: "Inside an oval frame is a grey sket..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Inside an oval frame is a grey sketch of a curly-haired girl enthusiastically riding an industrial drill. It's churning up hard chunks of rocky ground and scattering them into the air. In the hole created beneath is a silvery river of liquid metal.
